  "description": "The bird was large and bulky, similar in size to nearby AHGUs and noticeably larger then CAGUs swimming nearby. It had a very thick bill especially toward the tip, maybe slightly shorter then AHGU next to it. Overall the head and upper chest were very streaky. The bird also had distinctly dark eyes. The mantle was pale gray and the primaries seemed to be just a bit darker then the mantle. While flapping the primaries also appeared just slightly darker then the back.In addition to my pictures both Jason and Glenn got open wing shots which I did not get. These pictures can be seen at:\u00a0https://ebird.org/checklist/S283189538 and\u00a0https://ebird.org/checklist/S283206310",
